created.summaryHtml:
Note: The Checks API only looks for pushes in the repository where the check suite or check run were created. Pushes to a branch in a forked repository are not detected and return an empty pull_requests array and a null value for head_branch.

Check run activity has occurred. The type of activity is specified in the action property of the payload object. For more information, see the "check runs" REST API.
availability: Repository webhooks only receive payloads for the created and completed event types in a repository
Organization webhooks only receive payloads for the created and completed event types in repositories

GitHub Apps with Checks read permission receive payloads for the created and completed events that occur in the repository where the app is installed. The app must have Checks write permission to receive the rerequested and requested_action event types. The rerequested and requested_action event type payloads are only sent to the GitHub App being requested. GitHub Apps with Checks write permission are automatically subscribed to this webhook event.

bodyParameters.name: action
bodyParameters.description:
The action performed. Can be one of:
  • created - A new check run was created.
  • completed - The status of the check run is completed.
  • rerequested - Someone requested to re-run your check run from the pull request UI. See "About status checks" for more details about the GitHub UI. When you receive a rerequested action, you'll need to create a new check run. Only the GitHub App that someone requests to re-run the check will receive the rerequested payload.
  • requested_action - Someone requested an action your app provides to be taken. Only the GitHub App someone requests to perform an action will receive the requested_action payload. To learn more about check runs and requested actions, see "Check runs and requested actions."

bodyParameters.name: check_run
bodyParameters.description: The check_run.

bodyParameters.name: check_run[status]
bodyParameters.description: The current status of the check run. Can be queued, in_progress, or completed.

bodyParameters.name: check_run[conclusion]
bodyParameters.description: The result of the completed check run. Can be one of success, failure, neutral, cancelled, timed_out, action_required or stale. This value will be null until the check run has completed.

bodyParameters.name: check_run[name]
bodyParameters.description: The name of the check run.

bodyParameters.name: check_run[check_suite][id]
bodyParameters.description: The id of the check suite that this check run is part of.

bodyParameters.name: check_run[check_suite][pull_requests]
bodyParameters.description:
An array of pull requests that match this check suite. A pull request matches a check suite if they have the same head_branch.

Note:
  • The head_sha of the check suite can differ from the sha of the pull request if subsequent pushes are made into the PR.
  • When the check suite's head_branch is in a forked repository it will be null and the pull_requests array will be empty.

bodyParameters.name: check_run[check_suite][deployment]
bodyParameters.description: A deployment to a repository environment. This will only be populated if the check run was created by a GitHub Actions workflow job that references an environment.

bodyParameters.name: requested_action
bodyParameters.description: The action requested by the user.

bodyParameters.name: requested_action[identifier]
bodyParameters.description: The integrator reference of the action requested by the user.

bodyParameters.description: The repository where the event occurred.

bodyParameters.description: Webhook payloads contain the organization object when the webhook is configured for an organization or the event occurs from activity in a repository owned by an organization.

bodyParameters.name: installation
bodyParameters.description: The GitHub App installation. Webhook payloads contain the installation property when the event is configured for and sent to a GitHub App.

bodyParameters.description: The user that triggered the event.

bodyParameters.name: action
bodyParameters.description:
The action performed. Can be:
  • completed - All check runs in a check suite have completed.
  • requested - Occurs when new code is pushed to the app's repository. When you receive the requested action events, you'll need to create a new check run.
  • rerequested - Occurs when someone requests to re-run the entire check suite from the pull request UI. When you receive the rerequested action events, you'll need to create a new check run. See "About status checks" for more details about the GitHub UI.

bodyParameters.description: The summary conclusion for all check runs that are part of the check suite. Can be one of success, failure, neutral, cancelled, timed_out, action_required or stale. This value will be null until the check run has completed.

bodyParameters.name: check_suite[url]
bodyParameters.description: URL that points to the check suite API resource.

# hello-world-npm

This is a simple npm package that demonstrates the [Github Packages](https://github.com/features/package).

bodyParameters.description: The action that was performed. Can be one of created, deleted, edited, added_to_repository, or removed_from_repository.

bodyParameters.name: team
bodyParameters.description: The team itself.

bodyParameters.name: changes
bodyParameters.description: The changes to the team if the action was edited.

bodyParameters.name: changes[description][from]
bodyParameters.description: The previous version of the description if the action was edited.

bodyParameters.name: changes[name][from]
bodyParameters.description: The previous version of the name if the action was edited.

bodyParameters.name: changes[privacy][from]
bodyParameters.description: The previous version of the team's privacy if the action was edited.

bodyParameters.name: changes[repository][permissions][from][admin]
bodyParameters.description: The previous version of the team member's admin permission on a repository, if the action was edited.

bodyParameters.name: changes[repository][permissions][from][pull]
bodyParameters.description: The previous version of the team member's pull permission on a repository, if the action was edited.

bodyParameters.name: changes[repository][permissions][from][push]
bodyParameters.description: The previous version of the team member's push permission on a repository, if the action was edited.

bodyParameters.name: repository
bodyParameters.description: The repository that was added or removed from to the team's purview if the action was added_to_repository, removed_from_repository, or edited. For edited actions, repository also contains the team's new permission levels for the repository.

bodyParameters.name: organization
bodyParameters.description: Webhook payloads contain the organization object when the webhook is configured for an organization or the event occurs from activity in a repository owned by an organization.

bodyParameters.name: sender
bodyParameters.description: The user that triggered the event.

default.summaryHtml: When a repository is added to a team.

bodyParameters.name: team
bodyParameters.description: The team that was modified. Note: Older events may not include this in the payload.

bodyParameters.name: repository
bodyParameters.description: The repository where the event occurred.

bodyParameters.name: organization
bodyParameters.description: Webhook payloads contain the organization object when the webhook is configured for an organization or the event occurs from activity in a repository owned by an organization.

bodyParameters.name: installation
bodyParameters.description: The GitHub App installation. Webhook payloads contain the installation property when the event is configured for and sent to a GitHub App.

bodyParameters.name: sender
bodyParameters.description: The user that triggered the event.

availability: GitHub Enterprise webhooks. For more information, "Global webhooks."

started.summaryHtml: When someone stars a repository. The type of activity is specified in the action property of the payload object. For more information, see the "starring" REST API.The events actor is the user who starred a repository, and the events repository is the repository that was starred.

bodyParameters.name: action
bodyParameters.description: The action that was performed. Currently, can only be started.

bodyParameters.name: repository
bodyParameters.description: The repository where the event occurred.

bodyParameters.name: organization
bodyParameters.description: Webhook payloads contain the organization object when the webhook is configured for an organization or the event occurs from activity in a repository owned by an organization.

bodyParameters.name: installation
bodyParameters.description: The GitHub App installation. Webhook payloads contain the installation property when the event is configured for and sent to a GitHub App.

bodyParameters.name: sender
bodyParameters.description: The user that triggered the event.

default.summaryHtml: This event occurs when someone triggers a workflow run on GitHub or sends a POST request to the "Create a workflow dispatch event" endpoint. For more information, see "Events that trigger workflows."

bodyParameters.name: inputs
bodyParameters.description: Inputs to the workflow. Each key represents the name of the input while its value represents the value of that input.

bodyParameters.name: organization
bodyParameters.description: Webhook payloads contain the organization object when the webhook is configured for an organization or the event occurs from activity in a repository owned by an organization.

bodyParameters.name: ref
bodyParameters.description: The branch or tag from which the workflow was run.

bodyParameters.name: repository
bodyParameters.description: The repository where the event occurred.

bodyParameters.name: sender
bodyParameters.description: The user that triggered the event.

bodyParameters.name: workflow
bodyParameters.description: Relative path to the workflow file which contains the workflow.

in_progress.summaryHtml: A GitHub Actions workflow job has been queued, is in progress, or has been completed on a repository. The type of activity is specified in the action property of the payload object.

bodyParameters.name: action
bodyParameters.description:
The action performed. Can be one of:
  • queued - A new job was created.
  • in_progress - The job has started processing on the runner.
  • completed - The status of the job is completed.

bodyParameters.name: workflow_job
bodyParameters.description: The workflow job. Many workflow_job keys, such as head_sha, conclusion, and started_at are the same as those in a check_run object.

bodyParameters.name: workflow_job[status]
bodyParameters.description: The current status of the job. Can be queued, in_progress, or completed.

bodyParameters.name: workflow_job[labels]
bodyParameters.description: Custom labels for the job. Specified by the "runs-on" attribute in the workflow YAML.

bodyParameters.name: workflow_job[runner_id]
bodyParameters.description: The ID of the runner that is running this job. This will be null as long as workflow_job[status] is queued.

bodyParameters.name: workflow_job[runner_name]
bodyParameters.description: The name of the runner that is running this job. This will be null as long as workflow_job[status] is queued.

bodyParameters.name: workflow_job[runner_group_id]
bodyParameters.description: The ID of the runner group that is running this job. This will be null as long as workflow_job[status] is queued.

bodyParameters.name: workflow_job[runner_group_name]
bodyParameters.description: The name of the runner group that is running this job. This will be null as long as workflow_job[status] is queued.

bodyParameters.name: repository
bodyParameters.description: The repository where the event occurred.

bodyParameters.name: organization
bodyParameters.description: Webhook payloads contain the organization object when the webhook is configured for an organization or the event occurs from activity in a repository owned by an organization.

bodyParameters.name: sender
bodyParameters.description: The user that triggered the event.

completed.summaryHtml: When a GitHub Actions workflow run is requested or completed. For more information, see "Events that trigger workflows."

bodyParameters.name: action
bodyParameters.description: The action that was performed. Can be one of requested or completed.

bodyParameters.name: workflow_run
bodyParameters.description: The workflow run. Includes information such as artifacts_url, check_suite_id, conclusion, head_branch, and head_sha.

bodyParameters.name: workflow
bodyParameters.description: The workflow that generated the workflow run.

bodyParameters.name: organization
bodyParameters.description: Webhook payloads contain the organization object when the webhook is configured for an organization or the event occurs from activity in a repository owned by an organization.

bodyParameters.name: repository
bodyParameters.description: The repository where the event occurred.

bodyParameters.name: sender
bodyParameters.description: The user that triggered the event.
